1
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:13,740
(Day 5)

2
00:00:16,520 --> 00:00:18,000
Take a break for a bit.

3
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:18,550
I'm okay.

4
00:00:19,030 --> 00:00:20,150
(Female)
You stayed up late.

5
00:00:20,150 --> 00:00:21,150
It's fine.

6
00:00:25,150 --> 00:00:26,790
I'm worried that you haven't sleep.

7
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:37,210
Come on.

8
00:00:37,210 --> 00:00:38,340
Let's go to the dinning room.

9
00:00:39,720 --> 00:00:40,240
Sure.

10
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:40,630
Let's go.

11
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:55,630
I'll head back to the dorm.

12
00:00:55,630 --> 00:00:56,470
I'll be back.

13
00:00:56,470 --> 00:00:57,080
Alright.

14
00:01:12,550 --> 00:01:13,120
Who's that?

15
00:01:13,630 --> 00:01:14,400
Say hi.

16
00:01:14,950 --> 00:01:15,830
Go on, say hi.

17
00:01:38,510 --> 00:01:39,800
You're getting all shy now.

18
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:46,160
Good morning.

19
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:46,870
Morning.

20
00:01:46,870 --> 00:01:47,630
Hey, morning.

21
00:01:47,630 --> 00:01:48,120
Morning.

22
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:51,440
What are you guys doing this morning?

23
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:52,800
I'm making breakfast for Jiayi.

24
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:53,360
Sure.

25
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,160
Let's enjoy the rain.

26
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,080
What's on your mind?

27
00:02:14,670 --> 00:02:15,390
I actually

28
00:02:15,390 --> 00:02:17,160
quite like rainy days.

29
00:02:17,550 --> 00:02:18,160
Yeah.

30
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,160
There's a nice vibe.

31
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:20,890
I really love rainy days.

32
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:33,190
Morning.

33
00:02:33,190 --> 00:02:33,750
Hello.

34
00:02:34,670 --> 00:02:35,080
Yijia,

35
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:35,750
got a minute?

36
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,030
Let's chat away.

37
00:02:38,910 --> 00:02:39,600
Sure.

38
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:40,240
Come on.

39
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:40,720
Okay.

40
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,750
Morning.

41
00:02:52,190 --> 00:02:53,160
Well...

42
00:02:54,190 --> 00:02:56,030
You seemed a bit down

43
00:02:56,830 --> 00:02:57,750
this morning.

44
00:02:58,080 --> 00:03:00,320
Yeah, I felt pretty low all night.

45
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:01,470
Yeah...

46
00:03:01,470 --> 00:03:02,520
I could tell.

47
00:03:04,390 --> 00:03:05,880
I'm also kind of puzzled.

48
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:07,440
Um...

49
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:10,600
When that date list was announced,

50
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,160
I was pretty hurt.

51
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:13,360
And...

52
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:14,800
I wanted to ask you,

53
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,160
why wasn't I on it?

54
00:03:21,110 --> 00:03:22,470
Guess I got too greedy.

55
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:23,470
I wanted votes too bad.

56
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:29,670
Also,

57
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,190
I was kind of surprised

58
00:03:32,190 --> 00:03:33,630
that Han actually picked me.

59
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,160
I wasn't surprised at all.

60
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,470
I...

61
00:03:36,470 --> 00:03:37,750
At first, I really didn't know.

62
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:38,190
Literally.

63
00:03:38,190 --> 00:03:39,750
Can you hold the umbrella for me?

64
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:40,110
Sorry.

65
00:03:40,110 --> 00:03:41,110
I wanted to block the wind.

66
00:03:41,110 --> 00:03:41,360
Oh,

67
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:41,880
thank you.

68
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:54,830
I'll go another way.

69
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,080
Because, you know,

70
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:02,240
we've never been on a date.

71
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:02,830
Yeah.

72
00:04:04,470 --> 00:04:06,600
A first date actually matters a lot.

73
00:04:07,630 --> 00:04:08,630
In our usual daily lives,

74
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:10,030
I think we really

75
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:12,520
barely get chances
to be alone like this.

76
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,360
Don't you think?

77
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:15,000
But in the dining room,

78
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:15,720
and...

79
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:16,600
in other places...

80
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:17,000
But

81
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,200
when other people are around,

82
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,110
some things are just too hard to say?

83
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:21,920
Right?

84
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:23,000
So there's a lot you want to

85
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,110
tell me when it's just us?

86
00:04:24,110 --> 00:04:25,070
A whole lot.

87
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:26,440
I really, really want

88
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:27,830
to spend some time alone with you,

89
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:28,880
just to see how it feels,

90
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:29,790
and to have deep talks.

91
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:32,480
Like, even yesterday I was thinking,

92
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:33,110
well,

93
00:04:33,110 --> 00:04:33,790
it's strange,

94
00:04:33,790 --> 00:04:35,270
why did she show up the second day?

95
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:36,790
If Han would shown up

96
00:04:36,790 --> 00:04:38,040
on the first day,

97
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,550
none of this would've happened.

98
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:44,320
And...

99
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:45,720
No, I...

100
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,790
Let me put it this way,

101
00:04:47,550 --> 00:04:48,790
you can vote for her,

102
00:04:48,790 --> 00:04:49,670
one vote, two vote,

103
00:04:49,670 --> 00:04:50,920
or even three votes.

104
00:04:51,550 --> 00:04:52,720
It's totally understandable.

105
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,600
Because she likes you

106
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,110
and you're free to like her too.

107
00:04:55,110 --> 00:04:56,320
That's completely your choice.

108
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,720
If you both like each other,

109
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,390
that's the best outcome.

110
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:03,040
But...

111
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:03,600
It takes time.

112
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,720
If you still have

113
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,270
a chance for another date today,

114
00:05:06,270 --> 00:05:07,270
who would you pick?

115
00:05:08,230 --> 00:05:09,040
I'm not sure.

116
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:11,950
That's fine.

117
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:13,790
Just follow your heart.

118
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:17,550
Same as

119
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:19,720
when you cast your vote.

120
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:20,880
I mean it.

121
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,110
It's totally...

122
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,200
Just follow your heart.

123
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:29,550
I can sense every choice you make.

124
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:34,550
Ever since day one.

125
00:05:39,510 --> 00:05:40,270
You know yesterday,

126
00:05:40,270 --> 00:05:42,200
at that intersection,
I had to cast my vote.

127
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,760
I hesitated for so long.

128
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,160
I didn't want to go up there

129
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,950
or even leave my room.

130
00:05:47,100 --> 00:06:25,660
(Yesterday, Affection Delivery
of Zhang Zizheng)

131
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:43,860
(Zhang Zizheng > Wu Yihan: 3 weights)

132
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:47,340
(Chen Yijia)

133
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,070
It's just…

134
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,000
If you had chose to

135
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,440
go on a date with me yesterday,

136
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:56,640
maybe my date with her

137
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:58,040
wouldn't mean a thing to me.

138
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,790
Honestly, I was pretty…

139
00:07:02,790 --> 00:07:03,440
sad when I knew

140
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:04,230
your choice,

141
00:07:04,230 --> 00:07:05,160
to be honest, yeah.

142
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:08,000
So maybe it's just that

143
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,480
everyone makes different choices.

144
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,600
Maybe you just haven't met

145
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,640
someone you truly like.

146
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:12,880
You can take your time,

147
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:14,230
right?

148
00:07:15,110 --> 00:07:15,600
Alright,

149
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,040
it's okay.

150
00:07:18,230 --> 00:07:19,550
There's still plenty of time.

151
00:07:19,550 --> 00:07:22,320
It's fine.

152
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:24,320
Don't worry about it.

153
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:25,640
It's alright.

154
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,390
Okay, it's fine now.

155
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:33,470
We've got lots of time.

156
00:07:33,470 --> 00:07:34,760
There'll be more chances for us.

157
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,110
I don't have time anymore.

158
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,720
Do you really care that much

159
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,830
about surviving?

160
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:50,720
Is survival really that important?

161
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,270
We actually talked about it

162
00:07:55,270 --> 00:07:56,440
yesterday.

163
00:07:57,550 --> 00:07:58,720
I was thinking about

164
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,320
how I should cast my vote.

165
00:08:00,670 --> 00:08:02,670
They're talking about
a two-one type of vote.

166
00:08:02,670 --> 00:08:04,920
It might make everyone stay.

167
00:08:05,510 --> 00:08:06,270
But,

168
00:08:06,270 --> 00:08:07,830
if it's a two-one type of vote,

169
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:11,350
that's not how I feel.

170
00:08:11,350 --> 00:08:12,510
Because I always vote fully.

171
00:08:12,510 --> 00:08:14,200
I don't really want to...

172
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,670
you know,

173
00:08:15,670 --> 00:08:17,550
get to know more about others.

174
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:19,070
Whether I stay or leave doesn't matter.

175
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:23,070
I just want to find someone I like.

176
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:26,510
Like,

177
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:27,550
for Miss Zhan,

178
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:28,730
no one there

179
00:08:28,730 --> 00:08:29,450
is the right one.

180
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:30,000
But there are

181
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,550
over seven billion people
in the world.

182
00:08:31,550 --> 00:08:32,710
She will find

183
00:08:32,710 --> 00:08:33,670
her true love,

184
00:08:33,670 --> 00:08:34,230
right?

185
00:08:34,230 --> 00:08:35,840
We still have plenty of time.

186
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,230
Even if we leave this island,

187
00:08:37,710 --> 00:08:39,320
I'll still keep in touch with you guys.

188
00:08:40,230 --> 00:08:41,290
We can exchange contacts.

189
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,750
If romance doesn't work,
we can be friends.

190
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:44,840
Right?

191
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:45,320
Or...

192
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:47,090
Can someone who makes you fall
at first sight

193
00:08:47,090 --> 00:08:48,000
become your friend?

194
00:08:52,710 --> 00:08:54,280
No.

195
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:03,080
If you can make friends with someone

196
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:03,710
like that,

197
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:05,320
you probably don't like them that much.

198
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,030
If...

199
00:09:06,030 --> 00:09:07,520
If it were me, I'd feel that way.

200
00:09:13,590 --> 00:09:14,640
We...

201
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,110
We haven't known each other for long.

202
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,760
Honestly, these last two days,

203
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:20,710
the response I've gotten from you isn't...

204
00:09:20,710 --> 00:09:21,710
I'm aware of it myself.

205
00:09:21,710 --> 00:09:22,520
...obvious.

206
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:25,230
I didn't take actions
to spend more time with you.

207
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,960
It's okay.

208
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:31,840
Then...

209
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:33,960
You should know how I feel.

210
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:36,000
I don't.

211
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:36,960
I can't figure you out.

212
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:38,590
You don't?

213
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:48,640
All I can say...

214
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:49,400
is...

215
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,110
when it comes to

216
00:09:52,710 --> 00:09:53,590
dating,

217
00:09:53,590 --> 00:09:55,400
I think it feels better

218
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,760
when the interest is mutual.

219
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,180
Go ahead.

220
00:09:59,380 --> 00:10:04,110
♪Hard to believe
that you ever really loved me♪

221
00:10:04,110 --> 00:10:07,110
♪I made-believe that you cared
when you touched me♪

222
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,290
Come on, I'll walk you back.

223
00:10:08,290 --> 00:10:09,590
Let's go.

224
00:10:09,590 --> 00:10:16,270
♪I know I'll be movin' on in slow motion♪

225
00:10:16,590 --> 00:10:18,110
Do you like swinging?

226
00:10:18,110 --> 00:10:19,320
When I'm bored, yeah, kind of.

227
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,320
Swinging like that alone.

228
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:21,320
I really like it

229
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,710
because I feel like,

230
00:10:22,710 --> 00:10:24,030
(Day3)
when I sit on it,

231
00:10:24,030 --> 00:10:24,910
I'm doing something,

232
00:10:24,910 --> 00:10:26,110
yet I can still clear my mind.

233
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:28,640
I don't care about

234
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,110
other ladies' votes.

235
00:10:30,110 --> 00:10:31,080
(Day3)
But I am kinda

236
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,080
curious about yours.

237
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,350
So how did you guess?

238
00:10:34,150 --> 00:10:35,590
I'm looking forward to

239
00:10:35,590 --> 00:10:36,590
the final outcome.

240
00:10:37,910 --> 00:10:39,990
Are you worried you might lose
your beloved flower?

241
00:10:40,550 --> 00:10:42,840
(Day 3)
I'm gonna fetch it for her.

242
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:44,150
I picked them for you.

243
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:44,710
Thank you.

244
00:10:44,710 --> 00:10:45,710
Why two flowers?

245
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:46,670
Because

246
00:10:46,670 --> 00:10:47,760
one alone feels a bit plain

247
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:48,910
and kind of lonely.

248
00:10:48,910 --> 00:10:50,150
Better not to be like them.

249
00:10:50,590 --> 00:10:51,760
(Day 1 First meeting)
Thanks.

250
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:52,320
No worries.

251
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,670
Tomato and scrambled eggs.

252
00:10:54,670 --> 00:10:55,640
Dumplings.

253
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:56,820
That's gorgeous.

254
00:10:56,900 --> 00:11:02,220
(Day 2 Pool Competition)

255
00:11:02,230 --> 00:11:02,710
Hey.

256
00:11:02,710 --> 00:11:04,320
(Day 2 Delivering foot bath med)
You

257
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:06,350
fell into the water.
I thought you might need this.

258
00:11:06,350 --> 00:11:07,400
Thank you.

259
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:09,670
(Day 3 Competition)
Zhang Zizheng, come on!

260
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:12,080
Go for it!

261
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:13,520
Come on, you got this!

262
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:15,000
Stay steady.

263
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:17,910
We're just one step away from making it.

264
00:11:18,710 --> 00:11:20,320
It looks close, but it's actually far.

265
00:11:21,710 --> 00:11:22,840
I think a one-sided effort

266
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,110
isn't really a good thing.

267
00:11:24,110 --> 00:11:26,200
So if it's one-sided,
would you give up?

268
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:28,440
Yeah, because it's exhausting.

269
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:31,710
Love

270
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:34,440
is supposed to be one-on-one.

271
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,640
No one has that much energy

272
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:36,960
to deal with things at a time.

273
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:38,470
So when I feel like

274
00:11:38,470 --> 00:11:39,840
she doesn't really care about me

275
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:40,910
or want to know me better,

276
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,280
or even go out with me,

277
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:46,150
I think it's time to let go.

278
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:58,350
Morning.

279
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:59,150
Morning.

280
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,150
Have you eaten yet?

281
00:12:01,710 --> 00:12:02,790
Me?

282
00:12:02,790 --> 00:12:03,590
Not yet.

283
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:04,280
Not yet?

284
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:05,280
Yeah, I haven't.

285
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,400
What are you making, Yang Tianyu?

286
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:11,000
Just eggs.

287
00:12:11,420 --> 00:12:12,550
But different from yesterday.

288
00:12:12,550 --> 00:12:14,280
Looks like

289
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:15,590
you're making a fancy dish.

290
00:12:15,590 --> 00:12:16,350
Something tasty.

291
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,200
Got the vibe, right?

292
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:21,110
Are you making a love-themed salad?

293
00:12:21,110 --> 00:12:22,670
Exactly.

294
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:25,590
Check out this plating.

295
00:12:29,670 --> 00:12:31,400
